org.gridgain.grid.spi.discovery.tcp.ipfinder.sharedfs
Class GridTcpDiscoverySharedFsIpFinder

java.lang.Object
  org.gridgain.grid.spi.discovery.tcp.ipfinder.GridTcpDiscoveryIpFinderAdapter
      org.gridgain.grid.spi.discovery.tcp.ipfinder.sharedfs.GridTcpDiscoverySharedFsIpFinder
All Implemented Interfaces:
GridTcpDiscoveryIpFinder, GridSpiCloseable
public class GridTcpDiscoverySharedFsIpFinder
extends GridTcpDiscoveryIpFinderAdapter

Shared filesystem-based IP finder.

Configuration

Mandatory

There are no mandatory configuration parameters.

Optional

  • Path (see GridTcpDiscoverySharedFsIpFinder.setPath(String))
  • Shared flag (see GridTcpDiscoveryIpFinderAdapter.setShared(boolean))

If GridTcpDiscoverySharedFsIpFinder.getPath() is not provided, then GridTcpDiscoverySharedFsIpFinder.DFLT_PATH will be used and only local nodes will discover each other. To enable discovery over network you must provide a path to a shared directory explicitly.

The directory will contain empty files named like the following 192.168.1.136#1001.

Note that this finder is shared by default (see GridTcpDiscoveryIpFinder.isShared().
